1
00:00:06,459 --> 00:00:09,211
Kṛṣṇa is living, growing, 
developing, dynamic.

2
00:00:09,211 --> 00:00:12,559
Nitya-nava-navāyamāna. 
Nava-yauvana.

3
00:00:12,559 --> 00:00:14,247
Nava-yauvanaṁ ca [Bs: 5.33]

4
00:00:14,313 --> 00:00:17,658
[Krishna is Evergreen]

5
00:00:18,084 --> 00:00:20,784
Always newer, always fresher.

6
00:00:20,907 --> 00:00:23,922
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj 
would say,

7
00:00:23,922 --> 00:00:30,208
“Śyāmasundar means 
‘eternally green; evergreen’.”

8
00:00:30,331 --> 00:00:34,016
Because we were always saying, 
“No, Śyāmasundara means blue …”,

9
00:00:34,016 --> 00:00:34,904
but Guru Mahārāj said,

10
00:00:34,904 --> 00:00:40,763
“Śyāmasundar means 
evergreen. Kṛṣṇa’s evergreen.”

11
00:00:40,763 --> 00:00:43,238
So he doesn’t mean the thing
like the green colour,

12
00:00:43,238 --> 00:00:46,324
but evergreen, just always …

13
00:00:46,324 --> 00:00:48,621
When we heard about
the evergreen tree, we say,

14
00:00:48,621 --> 00:00:51,379
“Oh, these, some are green 
and then they go brown,

15
00:00:51,379 --> 00:00:53,771
but these are 
always eternally green.

16
00:00:53,771 --> 00:00:57,426
They’re forever green, 
they’re evergreen.”

17
00:00:57,872 --> 00:01:01,548
So Kṛṣṇa—like that.

18
00:01:02,795 --> 00:01:05,379
premāñjana-cchurita-bhakti-vilocanena

19
00:01:05,379 --> 00:01:07,999
santaḥ sadaiva hṛdayeṣu vilokayanti

20
00:01:07,999 --> 00:01:12,702
yaṁ śyāmasundaram acintya-guṇa-svarūpaṁ

21
00:01:12,702 --> 00:01:16,007
govindam ādi-puruṣaṁ tam ahaṁ bhajāmi
[Bs: 5.38]

22
00:01:16,007 --> 00:01:19,093
Acintya-guṇa-svarūp;

23
00:01:19,677 --> 00:01:26,516
His svarūp has acintya guṇas, 
inconceivable qualities,

24
00:01:27,412 --> 00:01:30,289
and the jīvas are His aṁśa.

